column2: Cloudy- the temperature is 70 degrees- 48 hours after 1.5" of rain.
Rained the last four or five days- hazy day- the temperature is 72 degrees- and the water is fairly calm.
Again had storms several days prior to reading- water fairly calm- and slightly overcast.
Bright- sunny- clear morning- just a slight ripple on the water.
Bright- sunny- clear morning.  Slight ripple on the lake.
Bright- sunny- clear morning. lake is very calm.  Some light green seed-like particles floating on the lake.  We've had lots of rain lately.  Had a 4.5" rain about a week or so ago.
Bright- sunny- cold morning.  Slight wind and slightly wavy.
Clear- bright- sunny day.  The water is calm.

Clear- sunny day.  The water is calm.  Lots of rain on and off this month.  Quite a bit of green particles seen suspended in the water.  Near shore scum like patches- scum appears to be attached to weeds below.
Overcast day.  Slight waves- warm and sticky.  Just taken on a Monday- many boats racing around over weekend.  Green particles still suspended on water. some green clumps floating.
Clear day- slight waves- lots of rain past couple of weeks- still small particles suspended in water.
Overcast morning- moderate waves- lots of boating activity since the 4th- very hot days over the 4th- now cooler with high humidity.
Cool- partly cloudy- moderate waves- lots of particles floating in water- also a very slight layer of particles on top of the water.
Warm- sunny morning.  Slight waves- has been cold the last two days- with some showers- nothing floating on top of water but small particles still floating in the water.

Lots of rain recently (3" one day- 2" another- and several days of 1") - little sunshine so day was slightly sunny- moderate waves- new culvert put in the channel (about one block from sample point) - lots of soil entered channel and lake is very high.
Hot- hazy- humid day (typical of recent weather) .  Moderate waves on the water and sunny.
Clear- sunny day- slight waves- have had lots of rain and humidity past weeks.
Sunny day- moderate waves- no boat traffic for past few weeks.
Sunny day- lake calm- had lots of rain recently- and boating is very light.
Calm water- overcast day- hot and muggy- lots of small particles floating in water- has been a rainy spring- and boats starting to churn up some of the moss-like substance clinging to the weeds.
Semi sunny day- lots of rain lately- and very few boats on the lake as of yet.
Partly cloudy- slight waves- and had about a week of hot- humid weather.

Calm- sunny- day.  Many small particles suspended in water- lots of activity in the channel (at the opposite end of the lake where there is lots of algae and scum) .  This is churned up and sent into the lake proper.
Today is hot and windy- water is choppy- difficult to hold boat in 45' of water- past three or four days have been hot and humid with temperatures of 90-95 degrees.
Overcast- slight waves- hot and humid- no rain to speak of for a couple of months- lake level getting low- lots of particles suspended in the water- boat traffic much more active.
Overcast day- water calm- lake level very low- we have only had one rainfall in past several months.
Today is clear and sunny- water calm- had a heavy rain two days ago (2.25") .  Prior to this it had been extremely dry.
Hot- hazy day- water fairly calm- some small particles floating on water surface- no rain since early August- and lake is low.
Cool day- yesterday had a little better than 0.5" rain (need lots more) - lake is calm and low- and little lake activity this past week.
Lake quite wavy- very cool day- partly sunny- had lots of rain the past week and 3" one day- 3/4" one day- and 1/2" another day- plus some light rain.
The day is cool and clear- slightly windy- lots of geese around (pulling out weeds along shoreline) - and little boating activity.
Cool- overcast day- water very calm- little lake activity past few weeks (no speed boating at all) .
Beautiful fall day- water calm- very little boat traffic- partly cloudy- probably will be last card - bringing the boat in.
First reading this year.  Moderate wind- no recent rain- some building going on at some areas on shoreline- and it is a sunny day.
Cool- clear day- slight wave action- water appears cloudy- however- this is Monday and their was a fair amount of boating activity over the weekend- no rain for at least 30 or more days.
Hot- sunny day.  Slight waves- has been a dry May and June.  Water has lots of small particles in it- lake level is low.
Semi sunny day- slight waves- have had no rain for several weeks- very cold and windy for this time of year- little boating or lake activity of any kind for past couple weeks due to weather.
Overcast day- has 1.5" of rain last week.  Lake is still low by about a foot and one half.
Overcast day- had rain lately about 5"- total weather has been very cool.
Warm- humid- dry- partly cloudy- and slight waves.  Past week we have had intermittent showers.
Clear- calm day- little or no wind- quite a few small particles suspended in water- has been very cool to cold (temperature of air) and little water activity.
Had a heavy wind yesterday- white caps on the lake- overall summer has been very cool. today is partly sunny- mild wind- and the temperature was 90 degrees.
Partly sunny- cool- fall morning.  Wave action is slight- not much boating activity- has been a cool summer overall- lake is very low.
Beautiful fall day- bright sun- little or no wave action- little or no boating activity.
Motor boat usage had stirred up some silt- disk showed slightly brown.
Taken on a week day- less boat traffic and less turbid water.
Partly cloudy and not too many boats on lake- water was clearer.
Calm water- full sun- and very little boat traffic.
4" of rain three days from reading.
6" of rain seven days ago- runoff in clouding water.
Dredging of the inlet channel was started two weeks ago but water quality has not been affected.
A lot of boat traffic over July 4. lake doesn't seem as clear this year-more algae.
Dredging taking place on west end.
Lake seems clearer than last year.
Channel dredging last year seems to have cleared up the lake
There seems to be more weed growth than usual
Lake is neither high or low but "normal" though it appears to be dropping.
Lake level dropping- it is 3 inches below the dam.
Less boat traffic- lake level is 8 inches below the dam- and there are still weeds over the lake.
Very little boat traffic and water at top of the dam.
4" below dam and no boat traffic.
Plenty of zebra mussels in lake on stones.

column1: very little milfoil after treatment this year

column2: 18" below dam- no boat traffic; Very few zebra mussels on pier and boats when taken out of water.
2 inches below dam- very little boat traffic this month
4 inches below dam- heavy boat traffic
Observations were under the conditions of mostly sunny skies- 70 degrees f air temp- south wind at 15+ mph.

column1: People assisting myself were- Heidi Bunk DNR agent- also Christine who accompanied Heidi.

column2: On the date these observations were taken- air temperature was 80.4' f ; East wind 10-15 m.p.h. - 30% cloud cover- readings were in 73 ft  of water.
I have now learned the necessary methods for operating the dissolved oxygen meter- from this point all data will also include D.O. readings. Thank you- Mike
